  "body": "Hi all,\r\nI am a newbie on this field and trying to setting Geth on my local.\r\nI am in a situation where I can't install Homebrew, so I have to rely on downloading from the official website ( https://geth.ethereum.org/downloads/ )\r\n\r\nFrom the website, when I clicked the button \" Geth 1.10.16 for macOS\" and I downloaded \"geth-darwin-amd64-1.10.16-20356e57\".\r\nAnd executed \"geth\" file.\r\nThen, it seems like downloading all blocks and when it downloaded over 100Gb, I stopped since I don't have enough space.\r\n\r\nI have seen that I can start with \"Light node\" with parameter `--syncmode \"light\"` but I can't find any info.\r\n\r\nIs there any way to start with light node mode on MacOS?\r\n\r\nThanks in advance. ",
