    "body": "Hi, are you running geth by double-clicking the executable? If you do that, it will run the process with no options at all, and you won't be able to use it. You need to run it from the command-line instead.\r\n\r\nOpen Terminal.app and type `cd ` (space at the end), then drag the folder containing geth to the Terminal window. It will now say `cd /Users/.../Downloads/geth-.../` or something like that. Now press enter. This navigates your command-line into the correct directory.\r\n\r\nNow run geth by typing the command `./geth --syncmode light`. Press enter to run the command. You can quit it by hitting Ctrl-C.",
